    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>sushi rice</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong> for 30 secs (use your hands to really wash the grains!), then set aside to drain fully</p><p>Add the <strong>drained rice</strong> with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low until very gently bubbling and cook, covered, for 15 min then remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/miso-portobello-mushroom-with-edamame-rice-and-gochujang-slaw/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Slice your <strong>portobello mushroom</strong> finely</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> on the diagonal</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/miso-portobello-mushroom-with-edamame-rice-and-gochujang-slaw/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced portobello mushroom </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 6-8 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/miso-portobello-mushroom-with-edamame-rice-and-gochujang-slaw/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mushrooms are cooking, add your<strong> miso</strong> and <strong>soy sauce</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>ginger paste</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> half </strong>your <strong>mirin </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>rice vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[255ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and gently stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>miso sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/miso-portobello-mushroom-with-edamame-rice-and-gochujang-slaw/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>shredded veg mix </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>gochujang paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>mayo </strong>and the <strong>remaining rice vinegar</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>gochujang slaw</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/miso-portobello-mushroom-with-edamame-rice-and-gochujang-slaw/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>miso sauce</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened and the mushrooms are coated \u2013 these are your <strong>miso portobello mushrooms</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/miso-portobello-mushroom-with-edamame-rice-and-gochujang-slaw/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>blanched edamame beans</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong>, then add them to the <strong>cooked rice</strong> with the <strong>remaining mirin </strong>and mix it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>edamame rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/miso-portobello-mushroom-with-edamame-rice-and-gochujang-slaw/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>miso portobello mushrooms</strong> with the <strong>edamame rice </strong>and <strong>gochujang slaw</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>and your <strong>black sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
